<br>
Magicians do get screwed in research by needing the previous spell just to make the new one, this is a well accepted and known fact.  <br>
<br>
As far as finding the other pieces, i.e. Jade Shards, Ice of Velious, Pearl Shards, Words of Coericen, Words of Dimension, Words of Duress, and Flame of Vox along with Gloves of Rallos Zek, you will see many people who just (to put it simply) don't know where to find these things.  And to be honest, no one does.  They are everywhere and no where.  <br>
<br>
Almost all of these things drop from a lot of different places, my guess would be they are totally random drops from random mobs that populate zones.  You don't see Gloves of Rallos Zek coming off of Trakanon, just the otehr things around the zone.  Keep in mind, that your best bet is the vendors around those zones, but with the advent of PoP you are in serious trouble.<br>
<br>
Almost everyone sells their &quot;crap&quot; in PoK or Shadow Haven these days.  I mean, really, rarely, do you see full vendors in other starting cities.  At least, not like you used too.  Remember when the Freeport Bank was the hub bub of traffic.  Now it's a ghost town.<br>
<br>
At any rate, because everyone is selling on the moon or PoP that 30 item limit on the vendors is full up pretty fricking quick.  And there are A TON of items people sell to vendors regularly.  Plus you have the problem of people just destroying it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Flame of Vox?  What's that?&quot;<br>
&quot;Mage research item.&quot;<br>
&quot;How much it worth?&quot;<br>
&quot;A plat or 2&quot;<br>
&quot;K&quot; ----  destroyed or left to rot at this point.<br>
<br>
Best thing you can do, and I know you've tried this, is to keep farming those vendors.  It's best to have a high level druid (like me) and use them to hop around from city to city checking all the vendors you can quickly and efficently.  <br>
<br>
Then doing and item transfer to get those items to your mage.  The other thing to remember is to put ALL your training points into Research.  If you don't want to do the research quests to gain skill, put every point you can into research.  Save them all and when you get to your next spell level, start pumping them in.  Should be able to get 20 a pop or so every 4 levels.  <br>
<br>
Next, go to the bazaar and farm those merchants in there.  Tons of people get tired of selling words that no one buys and they dump them on a vendor.  Keep checking.  Gotta be diligent.  It sucks, but whatcha gonna do?<br>
<br>
realize this... When it comes to being level 34.  You can buy two of the pets from vendors and the other two need to be researched.  The level 29 version of those is also vendor sold.  So for 34, you only have to research two pets.  they both require Words of Duress and then Breath of Solusek and The Scent of Marr.  BOTH of these items are vendor sold.<br>
<br>
So you see, if you can just make it till 34, your world becomes a little easier as far as research goes.   You only need to track down Words of Duress.  Everything else can be bought at a Vendor.  If you can't find all the vendors, trust me, they exist.  Just gotta know where to look.<br>
<br>
Peace.  Kastin.  Out.<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Forgot to mention.  These items are sold in the bazaar from PC traders as well.  Some people are kind enough to save this stuff and sell it to the mage comunity but usually the asking price is 10pp a piece per item.  This can get pricey.  So it's sort of a blessing and a curse in most cases.  It just takes a lot of patience and time.  I usually spend an entire day running around norrath compiling all the pieces I can, then giving it the ole college try and praying I am successful on at least one attempt.  The Level 29 Water pet is my nemisis but I did manage to get it on my last set of components.  Anyway, I wish you the best of luck in your Journeys.  and Shoot me a tell in game at ;lanys.kastin   (I'm also level 30)<br>
